ethod names, so I’ll consider renaming those variables and removing unnecessary types for clarity.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Reevaluating closure typings and stream issues**\\\\n\\\\nI need to think about the variable type annotations that were requested. While closures can be untyped, it seems a good practice to rewrite them that way. For instance, I could change the assertion from using typed closures to just pulling the bytes into a local list. I also consider switching to a Groovy byte array literal for writing data, but there's a problem with data streams—using `withDataOutputStream` overwrites the file instead of appending. I might need to split the output streams for better handling and address the compile issues with the byte list conversion.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_KSqfQivlVZIsk4ba1qQMGxKU|fc_0fa22a67994186750169ffe682a824819eacfa533072fb896e\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.groovy/groovy-nio/4.0.24/src/test/groovy/org_apache_groovy/groovy_nio/Groovy_nioTest.groovy\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"        Object lastLine = file.eachLine('UTF-8', 5) { String line, Integer number ->\\n            numberedLines << \\\"${number}:${line}\\\".toString()\\n            line\\n        }\\n\\n        List<List<String>> splitWithRegex = []\\n        file.splitEachLine(/:/, 'UTF-8') { List<String> parts ->\\n            splitWithRegex << parts\\n        }\\n        List<List<String>> splitWithPattern = []\\n        file.splitEachLine(Pattern.compile(':'), 'UTF-8') { List<String> parts ->\\n            splitWithPattern << parts\\n        }\", \"newText\": \"        Object lastLine = file.eachLine('UTF-8', 5) { line, number ->\\n            numberedLines << \\\"${number}:${line}\\\".toString()\\n            line\\n        }\\n\\n        List<List<String>> splitWithRegex = []\\n        file.splitEachLine(/:/, 'UTF-8') { parts ->\\n            splitWithRegex << parts\\n        }\\n        List<List<String>> splitWithPattern = []\\n        file.splitEachLine(Pattern.compile(':'), 'UTF-8') { parts ->\\n            splitWithPattern << parts\\n        }\"}, {\"oldText\": \"        file.withWriter('UTF-8') { BufferedWriter writer ->\\n            writer.write('one')\\n            writer.newLine()\\n        }\\n        file.withWriterAppend('UTF-8') { BufferedWriter writer ->\\n            writer.write('two')\\n            writer.newLine()\\n        }\\n        file.withPrintWriter('UTF-8') { PrintWriter writer ->\\n            writer.println('three')\\n        }\\n\\n        String firstLine = file.withReader('UTF-8') { BufferedReader reader ->\\n            reader.readLine()\\n        }\", \"newText\": \"        file.withWriter('UTF-8') { writer ->\\n            writer.write('one')\\n            writer.newLine()\\n        }\\n        file.withWriterAppend('UTF-8') { writer ->\\n            writer.write('two')\\n            writer.newLine()\\n        }\\n        file.withPrintWriter('UTF-8') { writer ->\\n            writer.println('three')\\n        }\\n\\n        String firstLine = file.withReader('UTF-8') { reader ->\\n            reader.readLine()\\n        }\"}, {\"oldText\": \"        file.withOutputStream { OutputStream output ->\\n            output.write([1, 2, 3] as byte[])\\n        }\\n        file.withDataOutputStream { DataOutputStream output ->\\n            output.writeInt(0x01020304)\\n            output.writeUTF('groovy-nio')\\n        }\\n\\n        List<Byte> bytes = []\\n        file.eachByte { byte value ->\\n            bytes << value\\n        }\\n        List<Integer> chunkSizes = []\\n        file.eachByte(5) { byte[] buffer, Integer size ->\\n            chunkSizes << size\\n            assertThat(size).isBetween(1, 5)\\n            assertThat(buffer.length).isGreaterThanOrEqualTo(size)\\n        }\\n        List<Object> dataValues = file.withDataInputStream { DataInputStream input ->\\n            [input.readInt(), input.readUTF()]\\n        }\\n        Integer firstByte = file.withInputStream { InputStream input ->\\n            input.read()\\n        }\\n\\n        assertThat(dataValues).containsExactly(0x01020304, 'groovy-nio')\\n        assertThat(firstByte).isEqualTo(1)\\n        assertThat(bytes).isEqualTo(file.readBytes().collect { byte value -> value })\\n        assertThat(chunkSizes.sum()).isEqualTo(file.size() as Integer)\", \"newText\": \"        byte[] initialBytes = [1, 2, 3]\\n        file.withOutputStream { output ->\\n            output.write(initialBytes)\\n        }\\n        file.withDataOutputStream { output ->\\n            output.writeInt(0x01020304)\\n            output.writeUTF('groovy-nio')\\n        }\\n\\n        List<Byte> bytes = []\\n        file.eachByte { value ->\\n            bytes << value\\n        }\\n        List<Integer> chunkSizes = []\\n        file.eachByte(5) { buffer, size ->\\n            chunkSizes << size\\n            assertThat(size).isBetween(1, 5)\\n            assertThat(buffer.length).isGreaterThanOrEqualTo(size)\\n        }\\n        List<Object> dataValues = file.withDataInputStream { input ->\\n            [input.readInt(), input.readUTF()]\\n        }\\n        Integer firstByte = file.withInputStream { input ->\\n            input.read()\\n        }\\n\\n        List<Byte> expectedBytes = file.readBytes().toList()\\n        assertThat(dataValues).containsExactly(0x01020304, 'groovy-nio')\\n        assertThat(firstByte).isEqualTo(1)\\n        assertThat(bytes).isEqualTo(expectedBytes)\\n        assertThat(chunkSizes.sum()).isEqualTo(file.size() as Integer)\"}, {\"oldText\": \"        file.filterLine(directWriter, 'UTF-8') { String line ->\\n            line.startsWith('a')\\n        }\\n        StringWriter writableWriter = new StringWriter()\\n        file.filterLine('UTF-8') { String line ->\\n            line.endsWith('t') || line.endsWith('a')\\n        }.writeTo(writableWriter)\", \"newText\": \"        file.filterLine(directWriter, 'UTF-8') { line ->\\n            line.startsWith('a')\\n        }\\n        StringWriter writableWriter = new StringWriter()\\n        file.filterLine('UTF-8') { line ->\\n            line.endsWith('t') || line.endsWith('a')\\n        }.writeTo(writableWriter)\"}, {\"oldText\": \"        root.eachDir { Path path ->\\n            directDirectories << path.fileName.toString()\\n        }\\n        List<String> recursiveDirectories = []\\n        root.eachDirRecurse { Path path ->\\n            recursiveDirectories << root.relativize(path).toString().replace('\\\\\\\\', '/')\\n        }\\n        List<String> recursiveFiles = []\\n        root.eachFileRecurse(FileType.FILES) { Path path ->\\n            recursiveFiles << root.relativize(path).toString().replace('\\\\\\\\', '/')\\n        }\\n        List<String> matchedTextFiles = []\\n        root.resolve('alpha').eachFileMatch(FileType.FILES, ~/.*\\\\.txt/) { Path path ->\\n            matchedTextFiles << path.fileName.toString()\\n        }\\n        List<String> traversedTextFiles = []\\n        root.traverse(\\n                type: FileType.FILES,\\n                nameFilter: ~/.*\\\\.txt/,\\n                preDir: { Path path ->\\n                    path.fileName.toString() == 'skip' ? FileVisitResult.SKIP_SUBTREE : FileVisitResult.CONTINUE\\n                },\\n                sort: { Path left, Path right -> left.fileName.toString() <=> right.fileName.toString() }\\n        ) { Path path ->\\n            traversedTextFiles << root.relativize(path).toString().replace('\\\\\\\\', '/')\\n        }\", \"newText\": \"        root.eachDir { child ->\\n            directDirectories << child.fileName.toString()\\n        }\\n        List<String> recursiveDirectories = []\\n        root.eachDirRecurse { child ->\\n            recursiveDirectories << root.relativize(child).toString().replace('\\\\\\\\', '/')\\n        }\\n        List<String> recursiveFiles = []\\n        root.eachFileRecurse(File