y_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Revising for clarity**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about using Groovy's runtime and ensuring that the native version is included. I want to rewrite the code to be more minimal by using explicit imports and avoiding static JUnit assertions. This could potentially simplify the compilation process. My goal is to remove any unnecessary complexities that might lead to errors, so sticking to clearer structures should help. Let's see if this results in better performance when compiling the code.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_XjmC1r1pqnmQrJhcC9Y7xUp4|fc_0fa22a67994186750169ffea02dcdc819eaa1645d4d7e4e840\", \"name\": \"write\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.apache.groovy/groovy-nio/4.0.24/src/test/groovy/org_apache_groovy/groovy_nio/Groovy_nioAppendSourcesTest.groovy\", \"content\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_apache_groovy.groovy_nio\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir\\n\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets\\nimport java.nio.file.Files\\nimport java.nio.file.Path\\n\\npublic class Groovy_nioAppendSourcesTest {\\n    @TempDir\\n    Path tempDir\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void appendsTextFromReaderWriterAndInputStreamSources() {\\n        Path file = tempDir.resolve('combined.txt')\\n        Files.writeString(file, 'start', StandardCharsets.UTF_8)\\n\\n        StringReader readerSource = new StringReader('-reader')\\n        file.append(readerSource, 'UTF-8')\\n\\n        StringWriter writerSource = new StringWriter()\\n        writerSource.write('-writer')\\n        file.append(writerSource, 'UTF-8')\\n\\n        InputStream inputSource = new ByteArrayInputStream('-input'.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))\\n        try {\\n            file.append(inputSource)\\n        } final